Budimex, Telefonica Czech, TPSA: Central Europe Equity Preview

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 
2011-07-26T23:01:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/budimex-telefonica-czech-tpsa-central-europe-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index  percent fell 0.5 percent, the Czech
PX Index declined 1.6 percent and  Hungary ’s BUX Index dropped
0.7 percent.  Budimex SA (BDX)  : Poland’s biggest construction company
is scheduled to release preliminary earnings for the first half
of the year. Budimex fell 1.5 percent to 81 zloty.  Telefonica Czech Republic AS (SPTT CP): The largest Czech
phone company may say second-quarter profit slid to 1.95 billion
koruna ($116 million) from 2.34 billion koruna a year earlier as
it cut prices to compete with rivals, customers spent less on
calls and regulatory changes eroded revenue, according to the
median estimate of five analysts in a Bloomberg News survey. The
shares dropped 0.8 percent to 426.5 koruna.  Telekomunikacja Polska SA (TPS)  : Poland’s biggest phone
company will probably say second-quarter profit climbed to 782.7
million zloty ($284 million) from 324 million zloty a year
earlier, according the average estimate of 10 analysts surveyed
by Bloomberg. Its shares declined 0.9 percent to 16.6 zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
